author: Paul Blest, Anne Torpey
title: Someone Got a Video of 12 Inmates Breaking Out of Jail Over Fears of Coronavirus
description: Those captured reportedly said they were upset after Gov. Inslee issued a statewide shelter in place order.
content:
Alarmed over the governors shelter in place order, a dozen inmates from a Washington state jail reportedly broke down a door, hopped a fence, and escaped Monday night, over fears of the coronavirus.
